    <svcsubproc id="hl1603016">
        <title>Operational test</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>This test is used to determine if the air conditioning system is properly charged with refrigerant
                    and the refrigerant cycle is functioning correctly. When a fault is detected, make the necessary
                    repairs. Repeat this test after repairs involving the refrigerant system to verify correct
                    operation.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The vehicle should be parked so there is no solar loading or wind for this test.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a thermometer approximately 30 to 60 cm (12 to 24 inches) in front of the vehicle
                grille and record the ambient temperature.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect a refrigerant recovery station (or manifold gauge set) with high-pressure and
                low-pressure gauges to the refrigerant system.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert a thermometer into the passenger side, left instrument panel register. Do not allow
                thermometer to touch the side of the duct.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Open the windows and close both cab doors.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Run the engine at 1500 RPM.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the climate control assembly as follows: mode control to PANEL, blower speed control to
                HIGH, temperature control to full COOL, air inlet control to FRESH, and A/C switch ON.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Operate the system for at least 5 minutes, or until the gauge readings settle.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Record the high-pressure and low-pressure refrigerant system gauge readings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Record the instrument panel register discharge air temperature.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to the following chart to determine if the refrigerant system is properly charged, and
                is operating within normal limits.
            </para>
        </step1>
